data.name: label5.Text
data.value:
The Batch Edit and Print tool requires you to have selected files in order for you to perform any actions. When files have been selected, the "EXECUTE" button turn green. If you try to press the EXECUTE button with no actions selected, it will notify you and remind you to select actions before proceeding. If actions have been selected and the EXECUTE button has been pressed, the program will carry out the tasks on all the selected files, and notify you upon its completion.
Progress can be tracked via the two progress bars and the text readout at the bottom of the program. The progress bar on the far right documents the overall progress of all the actions being performed. The progress bar to the left of it documents the progress of the current action that is displayed on the text readout on the far left.
When the EXECUTE button is pressed, the appearance will change so that the colour turns red and the button reads "STOP" button. When you press the STOP button, the current file that is open will be closed and all actions that have not been performed will be discontinued. Once the STOP button is pressed and all actions have been stopped, the button will turn green and display EXECUTE again.
While actions are being performed, the action selection pane and the add and remove files and folders buttons will be disabled. They will become available to use when the actions have been completed or when the STOP button is pressed.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
The current available preference settings are: - Create backups of each folder you work in - Enable/Disable notifications on task completion - Automatic folder browser startup on program load - PDF path setting - Supporting files path setting - Designed by/Checked by names
Backups of folders are made at the beginning of the program's running. They are not disposed of, and are only created. The user is responsible for deleting backup folders created with this program.
Notifications enable the user to run the program silently in the background without having to check on the progress of the batch actions. If an error occurs, the program will notify the user accordingly. Errors are not available to be disabled, as they serve a core function to the program's operability. Notifications that can be disabled are: - Task start - Task completion
The program will not allow you to create PDFs until a PDF path has been selected.
The program will notify the user of an error if it cannot find the supporting files it needs to run certain actions.
